Specified by:

                                     NodeRef child)

singleAddChild

public void singleAddChild(NodeRef parent,
                           NodeRef child)
Makes a link between parent and child. By default, if parent has a null reference for both it's children, child will become the left child of parent, otherwise child will become the right child of parent.

If the right parent of child is null, parent will become the parent, the same thing will happen for the left parent of child.

Parameters:
parent - the NodeRef that will become the parent of child
child - the NodeRef that will become the child of parent
Throws:
java.lang.RuntimeException - if the you are not in edit transaction mode
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if parent already has two children.

public void doubleRemoveChild(NodeRef parent,
                              NodeRef child)
